<subSubSection id="C9C6F1F7FF95CE45FF77F920DE7B3B40" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8163A27CFF95CE45FF77F920DE7B3B40" blockId="24.[136,778,1777,2093]" lastBlockId="24.[810,1452,1458,2055]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FF77F920DA513B25" bold="true" box="[136,258,1777,1803]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FE65F923D97E3B25" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[410,557,1777,1804]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smuzikae">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FE65F923D97E3B25" box="[410,557,1777,1804]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. smuzikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFF95CE45FDB7F920DA6E3B1E" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 34 D–F) are characterized by PA continuous to PI; PA more pronounced than 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FD61F8EBD8593B7A" box="[670,778,1850,1876]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FD61F8EBD8593B7A" box="[670,778,1850,1876]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF95CE45FF6FF88FDBB73B57" box="[144,228,1886,1913]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="20.[136,235,1240,1264]" captionTargetBox="[168,1414,201,1206]" captionTargetId="figure-290@20.[151,1436,189,1217]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 15. Actinopus apalai sp. nov., male: A–C MPEG 13184: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal tegular apophysis; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597269" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597269/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
A–C) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FE97F88FD9793B56" box="[360,554,1886,1912]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mairinquensis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FE97F88FD9793B56" box="[360,554,1886,1912]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. mairinquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FF95CE45FDC3F88FD9C33B56" box="[572,656,1886,1912]" captionStart="FIGURE 18" captionStartId="24.[136,235,1252,1276]" captionTargetBox="[196,1395,208,1216]" captionTargetId="figure-308@24.[151,1435,189,1228]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 18. Actinopus mairinquensis sp. nov., male: A–C IBSP 110484: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal tegular apophysis; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS- Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597275" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597275/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
A–C) and BTA in the middle of the width of tegulum as in 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FD63F853D8513BB2" box="[668,770,1922,1948]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FD63F853D8513BB2" box="[668,770,1922,1948]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; serrated area represented by four cusps distal to PI. They differ from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FEF3F81BDA273BCA" box="[268,372,1994,2020]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FEF3F81BDA273BCA" box="[268,372,1994,2020]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by more developed PA and from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FD0DF81BDA743426" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mairinquensis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FD0DF81BDA743426" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. mairinquensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by slender PA. They differ from those of the other two species of group 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FE52F7C3DAA63402" box="[429,501,2066,2092]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apalai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FE52F7C3DAA63402" box="[429,501,2066,2092]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">apalai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of abdominal scutum and by shorter PS. Females of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FB26FA62DE0C39E2" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1241,1375,1458,1485]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smuzikae">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FB26FA62DE0C39E2" box="[1241,1375,1458,1485]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. smuzikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 35 D–E) resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FCB6FA2ED88D3A36" box="[841,990,1535,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraitinga">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FCB6FA2ED88D3A36" box="[841,990,1535,1561]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. paraitinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
