<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FADFF96CDEFF3AF8" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1312,1452,1724,1751]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smuzikae">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FADFF96CDEFF3AF8" box="[1312,1452,1724,1751]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. smuzikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resemble 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FC66F932DF763AD2" box="[921,1061,1763,1789]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="itapitocai">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FC66F932DF763AD2" box="[921,1061,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. itapitocai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FB9DF932DF853AD2" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[1122,1238,1763,1789]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taragui">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FB9DF932DF853AD2" box="[1122,1238,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. taragui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of lateral swellings on inner lateral lobes of receptacles. females of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFF95CE45FC5AF8FEDF783B66" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[933,1067,1838,1865]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="smuzikae">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFF95CE45FC5AF8FEDF783B66" box="[933,1067,1838,1865]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">A. smuzikae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from all other species of the genus by long external lobes curved outward.
</paragraph>
